docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON, Sept. 12. -- The Daily Chronicle to-morrow will print a dispatch from Shanghai to a news agency of this city, saying that a native mob recently attacked the British Consul at Wenchow, in the Province of Che-Kiang, pelting him with stones and other missiles.

headline.main: A BRITISH CONSUL ATTACKED.; Officials, Led by Viceroy, Obstruct Ku-Cheng Investigation.

docs.lead_paragraph: BUENOS AYRES, Oct. 7. -- Thomas A. Eddy of Flint, Eddy Co. of New-York, who arrived here in June to establish a branch office for his firm, has made a careful study of the trade and agriculture of Argentina and Uruguay.
